This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as code generation and semantic parsing. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a modeling framework for these tasks. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it deals with generating executable code, and cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it involves constructing abstract syntax trees.
